We've teamed up with our label-mates to bring you a mix of heavy hitters and personal favorites from our discography.

The bands we picked on this playlist walked so that your favorite Deathcore bands could run.  Despised Icon has a lot of love for all the current bands that keep pushing the boundaries and have made this style of music bigger than ever.  Odds are you already know them so we came up with a list of bands from the early 2000's that were amongst the first to blend Death Metal and Hardcore together.  Enjoy!

We’ve been home for a week and we already miss it; the music, the camaraderie, the intensity.

Despised Icon has been our passion-project for over half of our lives and now more than ever, we realize how lucky we are to still have the opportunity to jump on stage and connect with you all. Shout out to all the fans, friends, bands, promoters, agents, managers, etc. that made this run our favorite American tour in quite a while. 

Huge thank you to @dyingfetusofficial for taking us out with them and @theacaciastrain on #MakeThemBegForDeath 🤘

Until next time...

📸: @stumuffins

We gave our friend @alexerian514 (of @despisedicon) one choice: sex or the saw. He chose the saw because the saw is family, so he’s hopped on our new song “Death Cult,” out Friday and based on ‘The Texas Chain Saw Massacre.’ Hit the ⛓️LIB⛓️ to pre-save one of our sickest tracks yet.

Our friends in @abortedmetal pay tribute to #TheTexasChainsawMassacre with their new single 'Death Cult', featuring vocals from our very own @alexerian514 🔥 The single is taken from the band's upcoming album #VaultOfHorrors. Check out the official music video, and give it a listen wherever you stream your music 🤘

#Aborted #DespisedIcon #AlexErian #DeathMetal #NuclearBlastRecords @nuclearblastrecords

So, who got a chance to listen to the new @abortedmetal single DEATH CULT featuring our very own @alexerian514? Let us know what you thought in the comments ⤵️

#Aborted #DespisedIcon #AlexErian #DeathCult #DeathMetal #Horror #TexasChainsawMassacre

After 2 decades of friendship, it was time for @colostomy_phd and @alexerian514 to do a song together! Drop a comment to let us know what you think of “Death Cult,” the ferocious collision between deathgrind and deathcore legends. The ‘Texas Chainsaw Massacre’ inspired song is the first to be released from @abortedmetal’s 12th LP ‘Vault of Horrors,’ out March 15 via @nuclearblastrecords.

The two vocalists first met in 2003 when Alex was drumming for Neuraxis. Two years later, Aborted’s first US tour was with @despisedicon, alongside @suffocationofficial and @cryptopsyofficial. What a lineup! Anyone catch that?

Relive it or experience the collision for the first time at Aborted’s ⛓️LIB⛓️ now!

Montreal Deathcore
Nuclear Blast Records
